Company Description: Community Hospital of San Bernardino, located in San Bernardino, Calif., has been providing health care and educational services to the area community since 1908. The hospital is a nonprofit, more than 320-bed, full-service hospital offering acute inpatient and outpatient care, surgical services, obstetrics and pediatrics, home health, behavioral health services, emergency services and neurological care for children and adults. The institution uses state-of-the-art technology in its patient care services. It also organizes a number of community programs, including weight management, diabetes, asthma and low-cost nutrition programs. Community Hospital is part of Catholic Healthcare West.

Company Description: Established in 1969, Country Villa Health Services owns, operates and manages 50 health care centers throughout the state of California. Its centers offer complex medical care, rehabilitation, sub-acute care, skilled nursing, Alzheimer's, long-term skilled nursing care and assisted living centers. Country Villa Health Services' Consulting and Management Services Division has been involved in the start-up of over 20 hospital-based skilled nursing units and currently provides management and consulting services to over 20 freestanding facilities and hospitals.

Company Description: Started in 1962, Rite Aid Corp. is one of the largest drugstore chains in the United States. Located in San Bernardino, Calif., it operates nearly 4,800 stores in 31 states and the District of Columbia. The company sells prescription drugs and a wide assortment of other merchandises called front-end products. These merchandises include over-the-counter medications, health/beauty aids, personal care items, cosmetics, household items, beverages, convenience foods, greeting cards and seasonal items. In addition, the firm provides numerous other every day and convenience products as well as photo processing solutions. Rite Aid Corp. has an alliance with GNC, a retailer of vitamin and mineral supplements.

Company Description: Located in San Bernardino, Calif., Shandin Hills Behavior Therapy Center is a 78-plus-bed nursing facility that offers a range of medical care services. It employs psychiatrists, primary care physicians and psychologist counselors. The center organizes various recreational activities and prepares strategies to reduce behavior problems. Shandin Hills Behavior Therapy Center is operated by SunBridge Healthcare Corporation, which provides short-term rehabilitative, skilled nursing care, long-term residential care and specialized health care services in more than 210 facilities throughout the United States. The agency offers speech, physical and occupational therapies, as well as laundry assistance and housekeeping services. SunBridge Healthcare Corporation provides assistance with daily activities, such as bathing, dressing and shopping errands.

NAICS 2 Description: Offices Of All Other Misc Health Practitioners

Company Description: Located in San Bernardino, Calif., Valley Star Children and Family Services is a community-based organization that serves children and adults with mental health conditions. The agency works in partnership with school personnel, county staff, parents and guardians. It offers school consulting, crisis intervention and after-school programs. Valley Star Children and Family Services provides in-home psychological assessment, case management and behavioral care services. In addition, the agency offers counseling services for individuals, groups and families. It is a part of Stars Behavioral Health Group, which has been serving the individuals with emotional disorders since 1988. The parent company s staff is comprised of more than 1,000 behavioral health workers, including psychiatrists, psychologists, medical doctors, social workers, nurses, therapists, counselors and teachers.
